<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBN-JETS-GIANTS-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TESTAVERDE WATCHES LUCAS GIVE JETS A LIFT
</HEADLINE>
  By JUDY BATTISTA   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. _ Vinny Testaverde and his banged-up toe
stayed on the soggy sideline Friday night, but Curtis Martin and
Ray Lucas looked as if they were in midseason form.
</P>
<P>
   Martin had 107 yards on 18 rushes and Lucas completed 19 of 26
passes for 286 yards and three touchdowns to propel the Jets to a
27-24 victory over the Giants in the Jets' final preseason game.
</P>
<P>
   But this game did little to help the Jets (2-2) find a third
receiver or to quell the lingering concerns about their defense,
which gave up 17 points to a Giants offense that sometimes seemed
to have trouble getting out of its own way.
</P>
<P>
   The Jets' defense has been suspect _ it was picked apart in
Green Bay and played only slightly better against the Ravens _ and
its troubling pattern of missing tackles and allowing receivers to
get open continued at Giants Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   In the third quarter, on the drive in which the Giants tied the
score at 17-17, Kerry Collins found Amani Toomer over defensive
backs Victor Green and Otis Smith for a 36-yard gain. Later, Tiki
Barber, on third-and-1 from the 15-yard line, ran for 7 yards along
the right sideline, aided by at least three missed tackles. Ike
Hilliard's 10-yard touchdown reception came at Omar Stoutmire's
expense.
</P>
<P>
   Even if the Giants' first-team offense looked frighteningly
error prone, Collins was superb. He left early in the fourth
quarter after completing 16 of 28 passes for 275 yards and two
touchdowns, with one interception.
</P>
<P>
   Powered by the running of Martin and the passing of Lucas (12 of
16 for 190 yards in the first half), the Jets were able to exploit
the Giants in a sloppy first half. Their first drive went eight
plays and 66 yards for a touchdown. Richie Anderson caught a 5-yard
pass from Lucas to give the Jets a 7-0 lead before five minutes had
elapsed. The Jets were moving well again on their second drive when
Martin fumbled a handoff to end the drive, one of two fumbles the
Jets lost in the first half.
</P>
<P>
   But even after Michael Strahan recovered Martin's fumble on the
Jets' 41, the Giants could eke out only a field goal, after their
drive stalled at the 17-yard line when the rookie running back Ron
Dayne was stripped of the ball. The Giants recovered the ball, but
not their momentum and they settled for a 33-yard field goal by
Brad Daluiso.
</P>
<P>
   The Jets struck quickly again. The Jets had hoped to use this
game to assess their receivers, most notably their newest
acquisition, Vincent Brisby. He caught one pass early in the game.
But, even with his soulmate Testaverde on the bench, it was Wayne
Chrebet who shined. On the fourth play of the drive, Lucas handed
off to Martin, who pitched back to Lucas for a flea-flicker.
Chrebet streaked down the center of the field, getting past
cornerback Dave Thomas and safety Sam Garnes. Chrebet caught Lucas'
pass on the run for a 52-yard touchdown that gave the Jets a 14-3
lead.
</P>
<P>
   On the third play of the Giants' ensuing drive, Toomer blew by
Marcus Coleman and evaded the late-arriving Stoutmire, for a
73-yard touchdown catch from Collins. The Giants were back to
14-10. And that's when they started playing like an out-of-sync
high school team.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
