<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-WHITT-COLUMN-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TIGER CAN'T THRIVE WITHOUT SOME COMPETITION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICHIE WHITT 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Combine the end of the week with the end of your rope and,
voila, welcome to Whitt's End.''
</P>
<P>
   'Twas the beginning of The End ... when golf's bewildered
hunters needed new tricks to catch a Tiger by the tail.
</P>
<P>
   Ali had Frazier. Seinfeld had Newman. Bird had Magic. And
without The Joker, Batman would've been just another middle-aged
guy with love handles and a cool car.
</P>
<P>
   Without a foil, Tiger Woods is lonely.
</P>
<P>
   ``He has to have challengers,'' former two-time PGA champ Nick
Price told cable-television's TNT, ``or the story eventually stops
being so compelling.''
</P>
<P>
   Instead of competitions, Tiger is turning the majors into his
personal monthly Golf Party Conventions. Sure, other players are
invited to fill TV time and appearances from past greats are warm
and fuzzy, but Woods is clearly the chosen one-and-only reason fans
stop, gawk and squawk.
</P>
<P>
   Problem is, while Tiger's presence is good for golf, his
dominance is bad for golf tournaments.
</P>
<P>
   Even before Thursday's opening-round 66 and yesterday's
5-under-par 67 at the PGA at Valhalla, he'd won 11 of 20 starts,
earned over $9 million the past 12 months and produced record
scores and winning margins at the recent U.S. and British Opens. He
recently played 28 consecutive rounds under par (take that Gabe
Kapler), made the cover of ``Time'' magazine and helped prod Jack
Nicklaus to play in Thursday's first round despite the death of his
mother the day before.
</P>
<P>
   Like Bill Gates, Evel Knievel and Jack Kevorkian, Tiger has a
monopoly on his industry. He's so good that his caddie, Steve
Williams, has earned more than $600,000 this year, which would rank
him 55th on the players' money list. Tiger has bludgeoned the
world's second-best player into Ernie L's, and Par-5ed the PGA into
a disheartened field of Pouters, Gripers and Also-rans waving the
white flagstick.
</P>
<P>
   Since his peers can't vote him off the island green, here's a
look at nine (the average margin of victory in his four majors)
suggestions the PGA might consider in order to tailor golf toward
the tailers and away from Tiger:
</P>
<P>
   9. Instead of girlfriend Joanna Jagoda, make him spend weekends
shacking-up with Jaromir Jagr.
</P>
<P>
   8. Give Earl and Tida one weekend off a month and bring in
Richard Williams, who would require Tiger to wear his hair in
beads, replace his trademark fist pump with a grunt, and read aloud
ridiculous grease-board gallery messages like ``Tiger is the man
who's got the goods ... I told you this century would belong to Mr.
Woods.''
</P>
<P>
   7. Every time he hitches up his sleeve before a 400-yard bomb,
make him recite the career stats of the original sleeve-scruncher _
'70s Pittsburgh Pirate Richie Hebner.
</P>
<P>
   6. Make him change his name to Tiger Irons, and an institute a
two-stroke penalty every time he uses anything stronger than a
60-degree wedge.
</P>
<P>
   5. Force him to trade coach Butch Harmon for new swing coach
Butch Huskey, and exchange agent Mark Steinberg for Mark Wahlberg,
who would immediately cancel the Nike partnership for more
aggressive endorsements of movies about boppin' booties (''Boogie
Nights''), broken boats (''The Perfect Storm'') and bossy baboons
(''Planet of the Apes'').
</P>
<P>
   4. Reverse his LASIK eye surgery and make him play wearing Harry
Caray's glasses .
</P>
<P>
   3. On Saturdays force him to ditch the snazzy Nike garb and play
third rounds wearing the John 3:16 sign guy's rainbow wig and
Bozo's big red shoes. And rather than his traditional red power
shirt on Sundays, make him wear a pink paisley Fatskin number
accented by one of Dennis Rodman's fuchsia feather boas.
</P>
<P>
   2. Since he is a rare golfer with no discernible pre-swing
quirks or waggles, make him hit every other drive with a running
start, a la Happy Gilmore. Using a blue Putt-Putt ball. After
bouncing it on his club 24 times like in the commercials.
</P>
<P>
   1. Substitute caddie Steve Williams with comedian Steven Wright,
who would usurp yardage booklets for monotone memos like ``In just
two days, tomorrow will be yesterday,'' ``Amateurs built the ark,
professionals built the Titanic. Go figure,'' and ``If marriage
were illegal, only outlaws would have in-laws.''
</P>
<P>
   If those don't produce parity, send over Michael Jordan to
discuss chasing Tiger's unrealized baseball dream. \Nsubheds:CARNAC
THE CRAZY Answer: Tim Seder, Reggie White and Patrick Ewing.
</P>
<P>
   Question: Name a teacher kicker, a preacher tricker and a
feature Knicker? \Nsubheds:BEST AND WORST Best call: The NBA
reducing fourth-quarter timeouts from four to three and eliminating
back-to-back stoppages. Now maybe the final 49.2 seconds won't take
longer than Shawn Bradley's learning curve.
</P>
<P>
   Worst call: Rangers broadcaster Tom Grieve often refers to
rookie Scarborough Green as ``The Human Highlight Film.'' Besides
the fact that Dominique Wilkins generated that moniker 15 years
ago, Green was hitting .183 with 0 homers, 4 runs batted in and
very few highlights late last week. \Nsubheds:NUMERICAL NON-SENSE
17: Players on the Mavericks roster.
</P>
<P>
   0: Legitimate centers on the Mavericks roster. \Nsubheds:WHY DID
THE CHICKEN CROSS THE ROAD? To find out why it's foul to be fair.
</P>
<P>
   In 1974 Little League of America lost a lawsuit which resulted
in all its sports leagues becoming non-gender specific, paving the
way in 1984 for a girl to play in the Little League Baseball World
Series. Fast-forward 16 years and the ``equal rights'' message has
become muddled. Little League Softball World Series teams are
threatening to boycott this year's tournament because _ of all the
nerve _ 16-year-old boys are playing for the team from Arizona. The
ridiculous claim of the protesting teams: ``It's not fair.'' Rule
that one a whine drive for a double (standard). \Nsubheds:END OF
THE END Snow White couldn't have been far from The North Dallas
Athletic Club last week, because two of her dwarfs (Michael
``Dopey'' Irvin and Sam ``Sleepy'' Perkins ) were working out
together. ... Second-most impressive local streak behind Gabe
Kapler's is the fact that Fort Worth property taxes decreased for
the sixth consecutive year. ... Got this friend who's always asking
to be Frank (Layden) with me, and he says the Russian Kursk is the
worst sub since Pete Myers' sinking performance for an injured
Michael Jordan.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
