<SLUG> BC-IRAN-MEDIA-REVIEW-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
THE FUNNY, BUT FICTIONAL, MULLAH 
</HEADLINE>
   (The Week in Review)  
 (NOTE TO INTERNATIONAL CLIENTS: For international clients' use by
special arrangement only. Asian and European points: contact Karl
Horwitz in Paris for details and prices (Phone: 47 42 17 11; FAX:
47-42-80-44). Latin American points: contact the Los Angeles office
(Phone: 310-996-0075; FAX: 310-996-0089)  
 By SUSAN SACHS   
 c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   CAIRO, Egypt _ In the classic Iranian children's tale, the
fictional Mullah Nasreddin rode his donkey facing backwards but
arrived at his destination all the same. He delighted in taking
advantage of the villagers who, in their turn, poked fun at him. He
