without trouble. But it only takes one to stir public ire. And this
year, the one that got away, a 43,000-acre blaze set by the
National Park Service near Los Alamos, N.M., destroyed more than
200 homes.
</P>
<P>
   And no matter how convinced the experts are that Los Alamos was
an exception, the fires now raging in every state of the West look
horrific on television, blackening national treasures like Mesa
Verde National Park and raining embers on popular campgrounds.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-19-00 1110EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
