   THE EXHIBIT
</P>
<P>
   ``Papunya Tula:
</P>
<P>
   Genesis and Genius''
</P>
<P>
   The first major exhibition tracing the beginnings of the
Aboriginal art movement of the Australian desert continues through
Nov. 12 at the Art Gallery of New South Wales in Sydney. ``Water
Dreaming at Kalipinya,'' the painting that recently sold for a
record price, is in the show. Afterward, it will be part of an
exhibition touring the United States.
</P>
<P>
   Jim Auchmutey writes for the Atlanta Journal-Constitution.
</P>
