   CHENEY _ WASHINGTON _ Cursory looks at Dick Cheney's voting
record reveal a very conservative record on certain social issues.
But examining his full record across a broad spectrum illustrates
he was even more of a voice in the wilderness. (Sherman, Cox News
Service)
</P>
<P>
   JEWS-AMERICA _ WASHINGTON _ Only in America . . . is the
elliptical refrain that immigrants and their descendants use to
thank their lucky stars that they are here in the land of
opportunity. ``Only in America, right?'' Joseph Lieberman asked
cheering delegates in Los Angeles the other night, suggesting that
the U.S. is the one nation in which the grandson of Jewish
immigrants could grow up to be the Democratic vice presidential
candidate. (Sherman, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ADULT-STUDENTS _ WASHINGTON _ Older students are changing higher
education, and it is changing them. This fall, more than 40 percent
of the students at the nation's 2-year and 4-year colleges and
universities will be 25 or older, according to the Education
Department. Most of them work, commute to classes and raise kids.
Why and where they go, and what the impact is. (Mollison, Cox News
Service) WITH PHOTOS. WITH ADULT-DATA _ Graphics material.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   ADULT-SINCLAIR _ DAYTON, Ohio _ On campus or via the internet,
students from near and far flock to Sinclair Community College, the
only two-year college among six cited nationally for ``best
practices'' in serving adult students. Its 21,000 students include
8,000 in their 20s, 3,700 in their 30s and 4,000 older than that.
How Sinclair accommodates their needs. (Jo Smith, Cox News Service)
</P>
