<P>
   RUSSIA-SUB _ LONDON _ The latest developments on the efforts to
rescue the 118-member crew of the Russian navy sub Kursk, as the
British mini-submarine arrives on the scene to aid in the rescue.
Russian navy officials are saying, however, that there is little or
no chance of finding anyone alive on the vessel sitting at the
bottom of the Barents Sea about 350 feet below the stormy surface.
Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service)
