</P>
<P>
   GARCIA-COLUMN _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Minorities watching the recently
concluded political conventions may be forgiven if they feel a
little giddy from all the attention from their new-found Republican
and Democratic suitors. But those who have had the good fortune to
experience romance know that courtships always produce hyperbole.
(Garcia, Austin American-Statesman) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   TEEPEN-COLUMN _ The first report on a law passed by Congress in
1988 to curb abuses by the IRS is in and it turns out that of the
830 formal complaints of IRS abuse, not one _ zero, zilch, nada _
panned out. Worse, it seems the fix has had consequences more
perverse than purposeful. (Tom Teepen is national correspondent for
Cox Newspapers.) MOVES THURSDAY.
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN _ Howard Kleinberg's column is not available
this week.
</P>
<P>
   GLASS-COLUMN _ (Andy Glass is a columnist for Cox News Service
in the Washington bureau.) MOVES THURSDAY.
