<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SOC-SIDEKICKS-HOTSHOTS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
DALLAS SIDEKICKS DEFEAT HOUSTON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By RICK MAUCH 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ On a night when Internet history was made, the Dallas
Sidekicks won in the rarest of situations.
</P>
<P>
   Last night's 6-3 victory against the Houston Hotshots in a World
Indoor Soccer League game was the first professional soccer league
game broadcast in streaming video on the internet. It also had no
scoring from Tatu or David Doyle, but Rusty Troy recorded his first
hat trick since 1998 and Nick Stavrou scored five points on two
goals and three assists.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've always been more of an offensive defender,'' Troy said.
``The first one (on a power play) got me going. On the second, I
almost acted like a forward. He (Houston goalkeeper Terry Waldorf)
was giving me the shot, so I slapped it by.''
</P>
<P>
   The Sidekicks (2-1) also played their best defense of the
still-young season. They held the Hotshots 1-1) scoreless in the
second half after having been scored on in each of the season's
first 14 quarters. Tatu and Troy both gave much of the credit to
the Dallas defenders, who controlled the ball for most of the
second half.
</P>
<P>
   ``In the game today, you don't just play offense or defense and
that's it,'' Tatu said. ``The defense has to move the ball around.
Tonight, they did a great job of coming forward.''
</P>
<P>
   Troy's second goal, at eight minutes and 15 seconds of the third
quarter, came as a result of Stavrou's third assist and gave Dallas
the lead for good at 4-3. Each player would add an insurance goal
in the closing period.
</P>
<P>
   Tatu led the WISL in scoring last season with 67 points (27
goals, 40 assists) and Doyle was the league MVP after leading in
goals (29).Tatu has three assists this season, but is still looking
for his first goal, while Doyle has two goals and two assists.
</P>
<P>
   The Sidekicks got a scare when goalkeeper Sagu went down and
laid on the turf for about five minutes following a collision with
a Houston player in the second quarter. He did not leave the game,
but did suffer a bruised tibia in his right leg.
Sidekicks 6, Hotshots 3
Houston 2 1 0 0 _ 3 Dallas 2 1 1 2 _ 6
</P>
<P>
   First quarter _ 1. Dal, Stavrou (Woodberry), 2:50; 2. Hou,
Leone, 4:42; 3. Dal, Shamu (Stavrou), 9:25; 4. Hou, Stewart
(Regier), 13:43.
</P>
<P>
   Second quarter _ 5. Hou, Perez (Leone), pp, 7:08; 6. Dal, Troy
(Stavrou), pp, 13:35. Penalties _ Campbell, Hou (unsportsmanlike
conduct), :39; Alvarado, Dal (unsportsmanlike conduct), :39; Team,
Dal (too many men on field), 5:38; Heth, Hou (boarding), 9:32;
Moreno, Hou (kicking), 12:18.
</P>
<P>
   Third quarter _ 7. Dal, Troy (Stavrou), 8:15. Penalties _ Heth,
Hou (tripping), 8:56.
</P>
<P>
   Fourth quarter _ 8. Dal, Stavrou (Fabio), 11:03; 9. Dal, Troy,
12:22.
</P>
<P>
   Shots _ Hou: 12-11-8-7 _ 38, Dal 10-15-12-10 _ 47. Power-play
opportunities _ Hou: 1 of 1, Dal: 1 of 3. Goalkeepers _ Hou:
Waldorf 1-1 (21saves), Dal: Sagu 2-1 (23 saves). Blocks _ Hou:
4-6-6-4 _ 20, Dal: 3-3-5-1 _ 12. Fouls _ Hou: 5-6-2-3 _ 16, Dal:
5-5-9-1 _ 20. Assistant referee _ Mills. Referee _ Dippolito. Sr.
referee _ Terry. Att. _ 6,432.
nn
</P>
